My meme

It was really awesome to finally getting rid of all bugs and run my R code smoothly. Therefore, I decided to create a little meme to express my feelings.

Enjoy yourself !! 

# Load the magick package
library(magick)

# Define the image URLs and text to be used in the meme
image_url <- "https://imagemagick.org/image/wizard.png"
top_text <- "When you write"
bottom_text <- "R code that works the first time"

# Read the image from the URL and create a blank image for the text
meme_image <- image_read(image_url) %>%
  image_scale(300) %>%
  image_rotate(90) %>%
  # Add a border around the image
  image_border("black", "10x10")

meme_text <- image_blank(width = 620, height = 320, color = "black") %>%
  image_annotate(text = top_text, gravity = "north", size = 40, color = "white") %>%
  image_annotate(text = bottom_text, gravity = "south", size = 40, color = "white")

# Combine the image and the blank image with texts to create the my_meme project and export the png file.
meme_vector <- c(meme_image, meme_text)
my_meme <- image_append(meme_vector) %>%
  image_write("my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

After browsing lots of colorful GIFs, I mad a quite straight forward one. The GIF will change color over time with simple text annotated.

Enjoy yourself !! 

library(magick)

# create four frames with different colors and text
frame1 <- image_blank(200, 200, "#FF0000") %>%
  image_annotate("Frame 1", size = 20, color = "#FFFFFF", gravity = "center")

frame2 <- image_blank(200, 200, "#00FF00") %>%
  image_annotate("Frame 2", size = 20, color = "#FFFFFF", gravity = "center")

frame3 <- image_blank(200, 200, "#0000FF") %>%
  image_annotate("Frame 3", size = 20, color = "#FFFFFF", gravity = "center")

frame4 <- image_blank(200, 200, "#FFFF00") %>%
  image_annotate("Frame 4", size = 20, color = "#FFFFFF", gravity = "center")


frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

# create and save the animation as a GIF file
my_gif <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1) %>%
  image_write("my_animation.gif")
